Class Oxidation<T extends Organic>

Direct Known Subclasses:
OxidationDoc
public abstract class Oxidation<T extends Organic> extends Reaction implements OxidationConfiguration
The Oxidation class represents an abstract implementation of the OxidationConfiguration interface, providing common functionality for configuring oxidation reactions in freshwater systems.

This class extends the Reaction class and introduces a generic type parameter T representing the specific organic chemical entity involved in the oxidation reaction. The organicCompound field is autowired to a bean of type T, ensuring that the oxidation rate can be calculated based on the specific implementation of the Organic.getOxidationRate() method in the associated organic compound.

  • Method Details

    • getRate

      public final double getRate(double[] y)
      Calculates and returns the rate of oxidation for the associated organicCompound. This method is overridden from the Reaction.getRate(double[]) method and is specific to oxidation reactions.

      The oxidation rate is determined by invoking the getOxidationRate() method on the organicCompound. It relies on the implementation provided by the class representing the organic chemical entity.

      Specified by:
      getRate in class Reaction
      Parameters:
      y - An array representing the concentrations of chemical species involved in the reaction.
      Returns:
      The calculated rate of oxidation for the associated organicCompound.
